helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Antonio Garcia,
I just checked again and you are enrolled in the correct classes. MA___231__101 has not been activated by the professor. It appears he is not using Blackboard. The same is true with PH___2021_081. The professor has not activated the Blackboard course, so I assume he is not using the system for the class. If they are not activated, you will not see them.
As for the 3 classes you are not enrolled in - those professors would have to remove you from the course. Blackboard does not remove students from courses, even if they are enrolled in different courses - so, because you were initially enrolled in those courses before your schedule was changed, you are in the Blackboard sections until the professor removes you. You can contact those professors to have your account removed from their courses.
Alternatively, you can choose which courses appear in your own Blackboard site by clicking on the "Gear" icon in the "My Courses" module and selecting the courses you would like to see.
I understand the confusion. I hope this helps.

helpdesk-note.body:
Antonio,
It doesn’t matter if you were ever really enrolled, the enrollment system, for whatever reason, had initially registered you in those classes before enrolling you in the correct courses. So, somewhere along the lines, a mistake was made. You are now enrolled in the correct classes, and you can see them in Blackboard. The courses you cannot see are inactive, meaning the professors are not using them. The courses you are not enrolled in can be hidden using the method suggested, or you can wait to see if the professors remove you from the roster. Alternatively, you can email the professors of those classes to request they remove you from the courses.
Blackboard is working as designed, although I do understand it is not working as you would like. ________________________________ Andrew M. Holmes, M.Ed. Instructional Technology, Information Technology Milwaukee School of Engineering University
Office: CC307 414-277-6765 414-312-1383 (cell) holmes@msoe.edu<mailto:holmes@msoe.edu>
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Antonio,
 
It doesn’t matter if you were ever really enrolled, the enrollment system, for whatever reason, had initially registered you in those classes before enrolling you in the correct courses.  So, somewhere along the lines, a mistake was made.  You are now enrolled in the correct classes, and you can see them in Blackboard.  The courses you cannot see are inactive, meaning the professors are not using them.  The courses you are not enrolled in can be hidden using the method suggested, or you can wait to see if the professors remove you from the roster.  Alternatively, you can email the professors of those classes to request they remove you from the courses.
 
Blackboard is working as designed, although I do understand it is not working as you would like.
Andrew M. Holmes, M.Ed.
Instructional Technology, Information Technology
Milwaukee School of Engineering University
 
Office:  CC307
414-277-6765
414-312-1383 (cell)
holmes@msoe.edu
 
 
From: helpdesk <helpdesk@msoe.edu>
Reply-To: Helpdesk <helpdesk@msoe.edu>
Date: Thursday, September 22, 2016 at 11:22 AM
To: "Holmes, Andrew" <holmes@msoe.edu>
Subject: New Reply Received - [#INC-10805] Blackboard Classes
 
Hi Andrew Holmes,

The requester has responded to the ticket (#INC-10805)

Blackboard Classes

Ticket comment
I was never enrolled for those classes this year. I am enrolled in statics, physics II, steady state, calc III, and Russian history. The other classes were classes I passed from last year. I already talked to the registrar and they have me registered under the right classes so the only problem here is blackboard.
 
From: helpdesk [mailto:helpdesk@msoe.edu]
Sent: Thursday, September 22, 2016 9:51 AM
To: Garcia, Antonio <garciaa@msoe.edu>
Subject: Re: [#INC-10805] Blackboard Classes
 
Hi Antonio Garcia,
 
I just checked again and you are enrolled in the correct classes.  MA___231__101 has not been activated by the professor.  It appears he is not using Blackboard.  The same is true with PH___2021_081.  The professor has not activated the Blackboard course, so I assume he is not using the system for the class.  If they are not activated, you will not see them.
 
As for the 3 classes you are not enrolled in - those professors would have to remove you from the course.  Blackboard does not remove students from courses, even if they are enrolled in different courses - so, because you were initially enrolled in those courses before your schedule was changed, you are in the Blackboard sections until the professor removes you.  You can contact those professors to have your account removed from their courses.
 
Alternatively, you can choose which courses appear in your own Blackboard site by clicking on the "Gear" icon in the "My Courses" module and selecting the courses you would like to see.
 
I understand the confusion.  I hope this helps.

helpdesk-ticket.description: Hello, I have sent a few prior emails but none of the options have seemed to work. The problem I am having is that I cannot successfully connect to party chats or online games with friends. I am able to connect to the internet, just not multiplayer online. I finally called Xbox and they told me this: contact your networking administrator to ask them about a DMZ being enabled for your xbox so the firewall within this network does not block certain packet types from getting to your Xbox to resolve this issue. I am not sure exactly what all of this means but I am hoping you do. If you could enable the DMZ that would be great (I think). Thanks, Jordan

helpdesk-note.body:
Jordan,
If you can provide me with the IP address of your XBO, I can check to see if it's somehow hitting a blocking rule. Please make sure that you are wired and that wireless in not enabled. If you are getting an IP address that is between 155.92.56.0 through 155.92.63.0, you will have limited access as that is the Guest wireless range. Guest wireless is not intended for use by students, faculty, or staff.
While we cannot add you to the DMZ for a host of reasons (your XBO would immediatly be rendered useless by the non-stop inbound traffic to the DMZ) , outbound traffic from campus is not normally blocked. If we can determine if you are seeing blocked traffic, it may help us locate and resolve the issue.
Please also fill out the ticket with your contact information so we know how to reach you outside of this ticket.
Thanks Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10833

helpdesk-note.body:
Jordan,
Thanks for the prompt response. Unfortunately, the IP address of your XBO was given to it by your router, and isn't part of our network. helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Brian,
It sounds like current student athlete data will be more useful than Admissions data for this project. The Registrar's Office would be your best starting place. Contact their office as they may already have class lists or reports that could be extremely useful in Algeria's project. If that doesn't fit your needs, we can give Algeria access in Jenzabar. That request would need come directly from Mary Nielsen though since she is the module manager for that area in Jenzabar.
I'm going to close out the ticket but feel free to respond to this email if you have any questions.
Thanks, Jasmine

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Anthony van Groningen,
We checked out L305 this morning - both projectors are currently working. An AV Technician is focusing them so that they are uniform. If it happens that one will not turn on, in the future, you can power down the system, wait 40 seconds, then turn back on. Normally that will resolve the issue.
We are scheduling L 304 for service as the main unit has a bad port, which is causing one projector to be non-responsive. We hope to have it fixed as soon as possible.
Thanks for your patience. Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10890

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 23.28 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.

Current Usage: 23.28 MB
Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB
Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB

Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:

1.    Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome
2.    Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….”
3.    Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password.
4.    Click web inbox
5.    Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages.
6.    Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder.
7.    Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window.
8.    Give it a minute and it should clear up space.
9.    You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.


If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Susan Bynum,
The issue you're seeing is because MSOE doesn't own or manage ADP. It's a service we pay for to run our time and payroll. This is the tool that ADP has provided to us, and as you've found, it often doesn't work. I have many of the same problems as you when I try to use ADP. I've been able to find some work-arounds online. This doc from the city o New Orleans has worked for me when I use IE. There may be other docs like this online for your browser of choice.
http://www.nola.gov/nolapay/documents/steps-to-fix-adp-etime-java-errors/
Thanks

helpdesk-note.body:
From: Gerry
Proffessor Ozturk came in. I went to the back to look for a docking station. I couldn't find any. Brian told me we didn't carry docking stations. I told the customer we didn't have them. He got upset because he had received an email stating that we would try another docking station, and I couldn't do that. I later looked up the ticket on FreshService. The customer was curious who sent the email, so he looked at the computer screen, saw Justin's name, and wrote it down. I am extremely sorry, I should have turned the computer screen away from him. I don't think that Justin was the one who sent the email. Either way, this whole thing is my fault because I didn't know where the docking stations were. If anyone receives an angry call from professor Ozturk, I am the one to blame. Tell him that the helpdesk technician that was helping him didn't know what he was doing. I am so sorry. Please invoke whatever disciplinary action upon me that is necessary. Someone later showed me where we keep the docking stations. Apparently, we refer to them as dongles, but they are really docking stations.
So sorry, Gerry
helpdesk-note.body-html:

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 24.31 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Laptop
helpdesk-ticket.description:
To whom it may concern,
I’m curious about Milwaukee school of engineering laptop. Do I have to return it if I’m not attending the summer quarter? Or do I return it on graduation? Would I own the computer once I graduate but once you remove the software? I just want to clarify the information about the laptop.
Sincerely, David Schrack
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
To whom it may concern,
 
I’m curious about Milwaukee school of engineering laptop. Do I have to return it if I’m not attending the summer quarter? Or do I return it on graduation? Would I own the computer once I graduate but once you remove the software? I just want to clarify the information about the laptop.
 
Sincerely,
David Schrack

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi David Schrack, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10971
I apologize for the lack of communication. Has anyone given you any answers to your questions? Feel free to keep emailing us. We are happy to help. :) My quick response to your question is: In general, you keep the laptop over the summer, provided that you are enrolled for classes in the fall. Anytime that you become un-enrolled, for any reason, you must return the laptop. The rules are slightly different for graduation, because we have a "gifting" process where we wipe your computer and give it to you as a graduation present, but this process still requires you to bring the laptop back to the IT desk before leaving MSOE. Hope this helps. :)
Thanks, Michael Logan helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-note.body: While faculty and staff acknowledge that the Helpdesk was incredibly busy during the start of school, I find it to be a very poor customer service experience to receive no acknowledgement/response for 3 weeks on multiple tickets. All academic departments were experiencing the same service. It would be nice to have a response of "your ticket is in our queue" or "we're experiencing high volume of requests, your ticket will be handled as soon as possible". Instead, many of us had requests just go into a black hole. We're told to call the Helpdesk, but on multiple occasions, no one answered. I think there are multiple areas of customer service that still need to be greatly improved.
helpdesk-note.body-html: While faculty and staff acknowledge that the Helpdesk was incredibly busy during the start of school, I find it to be a very poor customer service experience to receive no acknowledgement/response for 3 weeks on multiple tickets. helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I want to record my work hours in the ADP software.  I am having trouble updating java on my work laptop to do this.  I think I could do it in my office if someone from IT walked me through it over the phone.

I had my laptop reimaged in late August.  Not sure if that is why the java updates are so hard now.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Karen Bolton, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/10995
If you open up your Firefox browser, you can navigate to Java.com, and there should be a large link that will let you update your Java to the newest version. Make sure when you are downloading the software, just remember to uncheck the "free offer" of whatever toolbar it asks to install with the Java. Please let us know if this solves your issue.
Thanks, Michael Logan helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Passwords
helpdesk-ticket.description: Jeray Riffel signs in to my.msoe with Summer2016, but sign into everything else with the password she set. She wants to know how to bring them all under the same password.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Jeray Riffel signs in to my.msoe with Summer2016, but sign into everything else with the password she set. She wants to know how to bring them all under the same password.

helpdesk-note.body: by resetting her password via the portal
helpdesk-note.body-html: by resetting her password via the portal

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jeray Riffel,
You would be able to log in your all MSOE account through one password. To do so, you need to register your password if you haven't before by going on to pwdreg.msoe.edu. Follow the steps to setup security questions. Then you need to go to pwd.msoe.edu to reset you password. Let us know if you have any queries or stop by at IT help desk on third floor in CC. Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/11007
Jeray Riffel signs in to my.msoe with Summer2016, but sign into everything else with the password she set. She wants to know how to bring them all under the same password.
Peter Pfister Help Desk Coordinator 414.277.7202

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Steve,
Jonathan Kowalski put in a ticket with IT to make sure you are set up in Jenzabar. I see that you already have Jenzabar access. Have you logged in since we upgraded to Jenzabar EX6? You should have an icon on your desktop that looks like this:
You will need to double click on the icon and use your MSOE username and password for the first login. The second login is your Jenzabar username and login. I did have to reset your Jenzabar password so give me a call when you have a chance and I will give you the temp password. Also feel free to call if you have any questions.
Thanks,
Jasmine x2279

helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Cannot log into Blackboard, despite having active account. A professor has posted feedback on a project in progress.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mandy Runnalls,
A few things may be going on. Since you were staff, when you leave employment, your account is generally disabled right away; however, as a student you have 90 days access. Otherwise, if you have access to everything else, it may just be that your instructors have disabled access to the course. I actually see that your summer course has been set to unavailable. Are you able to login to Blackboard, but you don't see the classes? If that is the case, you will need to contact your professors to gain access to the material.
I hope this helps. Please let me know if there is anything else I can do to help.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi, Michael, Word is still locking up, sporadically. It will work fine for a while and then go through spurts of locking up where I have to restart it up to 6-10 times before it will hold up for a while. It basically just freezes and says it’s not responding and I close the window and either restart the program (which gives me all my data back) or restart the program (which gives me the information since my last save or an autosaved document). I used it today and it hasn’t locked up yet, but yesterday it was tough to get it going. It also often stops when I try to print something. It is especially vulnerable when I work with more than one document, trying to cut and paste anything from one place to another – I’m lucky if/when I’m able to do that. I hope this helps, and I hope you can help me with this problem.
PS – These notebooks have a funny feature. In the upper left hand corner, it often says “Autororate On,” Not “Autorate” mind you, “AutoROrate.” Very weird. Thank you again, JF

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jan Fertig, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/11041
I think I have a fix for your word issues.
· Try clearing Recent documents / Auto-recovery documents (file->options->advanced->Display) · If that doesn’t work, click file->options-> add-ins->Manage->COM add-ins->GO and uncheck BOX --- this will turn off box sync, but may improve the performance of Word.
P.S. I think "Autororate" is supposed to be "AutoROTATE" - and this is a very funny issue in windows.
Respectfully, Gerry TIER 1 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Twitter : @MSOEIT
"We are building a culture of Exceptional Customer Service"

helpdesk-note.body:
Dear Gerry, Peter and all:
I think the problem with word might be fixed, but I will come back if it starts to freeze up again. Reinstalling seems to have helped, but there was another problem that had me running to the desk on Wednesday. Peter spent as much time as I needed to explain the problem to me and was very patient with my failure to understand the process. Because of that, I was able to go and relax and know that I could write and print my syllabi over Thanksgiving weekend. Previously, Gerry was really kind and patient with my word problem too.
You guys, I don’t know how IT went from mean and nasty (Fall of 2015) to so great today: I have no fear of coming in, calling, writing or submitting a ticket. You have achieved the exceptional customer service: stay as great as you are! Hope I don’t see you for a reimage, but if I do, I won’t be afraid ☺
Jan Fertig

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Voicemail Mailbox Quota Warning
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.
Current Usage: 25.84 MB Quota Warning Threshold: 11.44 MB Quota Size Limit: 14.06 MB
Please reduce your voice mailbox size by deleting few items from your mailbox. The best way to do this is as follows:
1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu in chrome 2. Click “advanced” and then “proceed to ucon…….” 3. Log in using your standard msoe domain credentials and your password. 4. Click web inbox 5. Select and delete all, or the majority, of the messages in your inbox, this will be a number of pages. 6. Then click the “deleted” button near the top left to see the deleted folder. 7. Then click “empty deleted items” in the upper right of the white window. 8. Give it a minute and it should clear up space. 9. You can dial *XXXX , where XXXX is your extension, and it will put you right into your voicemail so you can leave yourself a message to see for sure if it comes through.
If problems persist or you have issues logging into the web page, please call the helpdesk at 7288.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Your voice mailbox has exceeded the quota warning threshold specified by your administrator.

Current Usage: 25.84 MB

helpdesk-note.body:
Professor Schaefer,
AD group access on these folders is hierarchical, so each folder below another inherits the behaviors of the one above. This causes problems because a number of students you have listed are members of the full access group for the top level folder. Adding the remaining students to this group would give them full access to the top level folder. Changing access from the top level folder would remove access from all users in that group, including the ones who currently have access.
Essentially, users in those groups will either keep full access or be added to the Read Only group and lose access. For the fine tuning of users you are requesting, it may make more sense to move the 2017 SAE Formula Hybrid sub-folder to Box and invite the students you wish to have access.
In short, there are only two groups for students in these folders: Full Access and Read Only. Changes on our side will affect the entire group.
Thanks,
Paul Fabian
MSOE Director of IT Services
fabian@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body: I brought in my laptop a month ago because it wouldn't turn on and when I came back 4 days later, to check on the status, they still hadn't even looked at it so the guy did a quick force restart in the back and gave it back to me telling me it works now. It turned on for about 5 minutes and then just shut off again. I brought it back the next day and they said they would send it to vanguard and gave me a loaner. Yesterday I got an email saying my ticket has been resolved. I thought this meant that they had finally fixed my laptop after almost a month and I could go pick it up. This was not the case. The IT workers could not find the laptop in the back so they were confused as to why I got the email. Also the IT worker that was helping seemed like he didn't know what he was doing and he was constantly asking the supervisor what to do. They spent 30 minutes trying to figure out where my laptop was and if it was still in vangaurd because for some reason my serial number didn't show anything when it was put into their computer. They finally came to the conclusion that it actually hadn't come in since they usually get an email from Vangaurd if a laptop does come back. They could have said that 30 minutes ago. So I am still without my laptop after 3 IT visits that have probably taken over 3 hours put together. All my documents are on this laptop and I have gone the first half of Fall quarter without it which has caused a lot of problems for me.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Script needed
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
I am looking for help in removing position end dates for faculty and staff with a primary active or active position who are not paid year round. Can you please let me know if this is something you can do for payroll?
Thanks!
Tracy Buczek Payroll & Benefits Coordinator 1025 N Broadway Milwaukee, WI 53202 Ph: (414) 277-7136 buczek@msoe.edu<mailto:buczek@msoe.edu> [xlogo-msoe_75.png.pagespeed.ic]
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello,
 
I am looking for help in removing position end dates for faculty and staff with a primary active or active position who are not paid year round.  Can you please let me know if this is something you can do for payroll? 
 
Thanks!
 
Tracy Buczek
Payroll & Benefits Coordinator
1025 N Broadway
Milwaukee, WI 53202
Ph:  (414) 277-7136
buczek@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Tracy,
I have attached the SQL script that will remove position end dates for any full and part time faculty and staff with Primary Active (P) or Active (A) statuses. This script will affect the IND_POS_HIST table in Jenzabar.
Step 1 will allow you to select and view all the rows that will be affected. This is good to look at ahead of time to make sure you have the correct rows to update. You may want to keep a copy of this result in case you ever need to refer back to what rows you are changing.
Step 2 will remove the end dates for those rows and make record of who is running the script and mark what time the script is being run. This part of the script is enclosed in /* comment out */ symbols. This prevents the script from being run on accident. When you are ready to run the script, you will just need to highlight everything inside of the /* symbols to be able to run it.
We talked about this request a bit back in July so I would like to stop by and go over the script with you to make sure this is exactly what you need. We can test it out in play first and make any adjustments if we need to. Jasmine

helpdesk-note.body: I dropped off my laptop on Friday afternoon and was told it would be ready for pickup by Saturday morning. I did not request a loaner based on the stated timeline. I went to pick it up on Monday morning, and was then told there was a problem and it was not done. I said that I needed it for class that afternoon, and was assured that it would be done by then. I asked to be called when it was finished or if there were any problems, and the tech took down my number. I received no calls that afternoon, and when I stopped at the desk right before my class, it was not finished. Luckily I was able to use my own laptop during class, otherwise this would have cost me more than 6% of my lecture time for the quarter. Tuesday morning I stopped at the help desk at your advertised opening time of 7:30 am. The tech on staff did not have access to my laptop and couldn't tell if it was completed or not, because he did not have the proper keys. If you say you open at 7:30, all services should be available at that time, or you should provide a notice that only limited services are available until a certain time. I had to wait until an employee with the proper keys arrived to finally pick up my finished laptop.
